    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's exactly that. it's too convenient. like, i literally just sent an email to the ethics committee about the offshore accounts and forty-eight hours later the MD is congratulating me on my \"leadership potential\" and giving me this office. it feels less like a reward and more like they're trying to isolate me in a glass box where they can see everything i'm doing. do you think they've already set up some kind of surveillance or monitoring because of the new office placement?",
